    "faq": {
      "type": "faq",
      "blocks": {
        "question-4": {
          "type": "question",
          "settings": {
            "title": "<strong>What is the difference between Hybrid and Venus?</strong>",
            "text": "<p>Hybrid and Venus are designed for different riding preferences.<br/><br/><strong>Venus</strong> is lighter, requires a lower inseam, and feels more nimble, which isideal for riders with a smaller build or those who prefer agile city cruising.<br/><strong>Hybrid </strong>offers a more grounded, stable ride with a higher <strong>440 lb payload</strong> capacity (vs. 350 lb on Venus). It also features a larger<strong> 864Wh battery</strong> for extended range, while Venus is equipped with a 680Wh battery. In addition, Hybrid comes with a hydraulic suspension fork, whereas Venus uses a rigid aluminum fork.<br/><br/>In short:<br/>- Choose <strong>Hybrid</strong> for longer range, greater payload, and a sturdier ride feel.<br/>- Choose <strong>Venus</strong> for lighter weight and nimble everyday riding.</p>",
            "highlighted_text": "none",
            "highlighted_scribble": "circle"
          }
        },
        "question-1": {
          "type": "question",
          "settings": {
            "title": "<strong>Is Hyrbrid's fork adjustable?</strong>",
            "text": "<p>Yes. The fork features <strong>adjustable suspension stiffness</strong> and <strong>a lockout function</strong>, controlled by knobs on the top of the fork.</p>",
            "highlighted_text": "none",
            "highlighted_scribble": "circle"
          }
        },
        "question-2": {
          "type": "question",
          "settings": {
            "title": "<strong>Does Hybrid comes with a rear rack and fenders?</strong>",
            "text": "<p>Yes. The rear rack and rear fender come pre-installed. The front fender is included in the box and requires installation.</p>",
            "highlighted_text": "none",
            "highlighted_scribble": "circle"
          }
        },
        "question-3": {
          "type": "question",
          "settings": {
            "title": "<strong>How to switch between Class 2 and Class 3 modes? Can I customize the speed for each PAS level?</strong>",
            "text": "<p>You can switch riding classes in two ways:<br/><strong>- Via the Heybike app</strong><br/> On the home screen, choose from three riding profiles: Eco, Sport, or Custom.<br/>   Eco = Class 2<br/>   Sport = Class 3<br/> Speed settings for PAS and throttle can be adjusted under Personalize → Speed Settings.<br/> <br/><strong>- Via the display settings</strong><br/>  On the display, the change can be made through manual adjustment of top speed.</p>",
            "highlighted_text": "none",
            "highlighted_scribble": "circle"
          }
        },
        "question_dcK38j": {
          "type": "question",
          "settings": {
            "title": "<strong>What is the warranty for Hybrid?</strong>",
            "text": "<p>Hybrid purchased from our official website comes with a 2-year limited warranty. For full details, <a href=\"/pages/warranty\" title=\"Warranty\">visit our Warranty page. </a></p>",
            "highlighted_text": "none",
            "highlighted_scribble": "circle"
          }
        },
        "question_CLnUik": {
          "type": "question",
          "settings": {
            "title": "<strong>Where can I find the Hybrid manual and video assembly instruction?</strong>",
            "text": "<p>A user manual card is included in the product package. Scan the QR code on the card to access our <a href=\"https://heybike.nextop.com/\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"https://heybike.nextop.com/\">user manual page</a>. You can also download from here. </p>",
            "highlighted_text": "none",
            "highlighted_scribble": "circle"
          }
        }
      },
      "block_order": [
        "question-4",
        "question-1",
        "question-2",
